00:12:19.132 --> 00:12:25.922
afternoon, nighttime, clear skies, cloudy skies—always cross-checking for tiny differences.

00:12:26.702 --> 00:12:30.412
They kept notebooks full of corrections for temperature

00:12:30.412 --> 00:12:33.842
changes that could affect the metal in their instruments.

00:12:34.742 --> 00:12:40.552
They also had to correct for atmospheric refraction, the way light bends

00:12:40.552 --> 00:12:44.572
slightly as it travels through layers of air with different densities.

00:12:45.342 --> 00:12:51.392
Any slip-up, any mistake, could lead to a miscalculation of the final metre.

00:12:52.382 --> 00:12:56.882
But perhaps the scientific part, the observations and the

00:12:56.882 --> 00:13:00.512
calculations, were not the greatest challenge the pair faced.

